Rebecca,

Thanks for reporting the problems.  The way I added the MATLAB files to 
the SetupCantera project (drap and drop) inadvertently brought in the 
CVS files.  I though I had removed them all, but I guess I missed some. 
  I&#39;ll delete them.

The equilibrium error is curious.  I&#39;ll look into why that happens, and 
see if I can reproduce it on a Mac or linux.

Dave


On Dec 15, 2004, at 12:45 PM, R A Hunt wrote:

&gt;
&gt; Fantastic.  Thank you so much!
&gt;
&gt;   I tested this on a XP machine without Fortran using VStudio .Net and
&gt; was able to run the matlab and python example scripts.  So far I have
&gt; only tested the zipped source code, and not tested the procedure with
&gt; code checked out of CVS.
&gt;
&gt; I encountered two problems, which I will document here and describe my
&gt; quick fixes (better solutions are welcomed.)
&gt; 1. PROBLEM: The first problem occurred at the step of building
